<br>
However, there are times when I &quot;WANT&quot; to keep aggro because I happen to have the highest AC and HP in the group.  In those times, I would like to have the option of having one song that creates aggro.....not have all our songs create more aggro...JUST ONE.  This way it is a choice.  It provides options instead of the same ol' crap day in and day out.  For those bards who never want aggro...easy solution: they never have to sing that song. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=calliopeia>Calliopeia</A></span><br> Posts: 182<br> <font color=#330000>(8/22/04 5:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19697.topic&index=102>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Master of Disgust</span><hr size=1> I like the idea of a taunt song like Taluwen has mentioned.  For the purposes that Taluwen lists, it would work best if it added a certain amount of hate and could be pulsed.  That way, a bard would give up the other songs in the twist if they need to build a lot of hate.<br>
<br>
The other thing I'd like to see that could be handled well through an AA is a snap aggro option.  Yes, this is Taunt.  However, if it were tied to mana (1200 - 1600 mana seems reasonable) it's use would be limited so bards wouldn't step on the toes of the tanking hybrids but it would be available for those times when the tank goes down but the cleric hasn't yet and the bard wants to hold aggro for a short period of time to finish off a mob.<br>
<br>
The current AA that adds aggro to our detrimental songs doesn't effectively address either of the 2 scenarios because it can't be controlled well enough. <p><center><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="2" width="75%"><br>
