<br>
To touch on a few issues raised in this thread:<br>
<br>
The AA for the mitigation rune should be group based.  This will go a long way in increasing bard stackability on many raids.  <br>
<br>
The AA for AE ramp should be changed to make the bard dual wield and double attack 100% for the duration.  This would be our burst DPS that many of us ask for, and I do not see this as imbalancing.<br>
<br>
Permanent illusion AA is fine, toys are a good thing, it reminds us that this game is not always about min/maxing.<br>
<br>
I am against an AA taunt for snap agro.  Please do not ask to have our agro in any way modified other than a song for it.  I would rather the agro AA be replaced by something that affects our songs.  As mentioned earlier, this would be a good place to dramatically increase the effectiveness of holding an instrument.  It is sad that you never see bards using instruments, since the difference between worn mod and instrument is so small, it is not worth it to give up melee.  Make this AA multiply the modifier of held instruments.<br>
<br>
Kanarian, Bard of Saryrn<br>
Impressario of The War Council <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lanolar>Lanolar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 1030<br> <font color=#330000>(8/25/04 1:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19697.topic&index=115>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aa</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>AA's - Overall, they look excellent.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
